page.title: 01Wretton, Norfolk Fenlands
page.content: the block comprises mainly reclaimed fen land. The soil is sandy, organic sand & peat overlying chalk. Nearly all is grade3 agricultural land. It is crosses by 2 water courses. The River Wissey & a main drainage channel flowing from the Denver Sluice. Wretton is a small residnetial village. The population is stable, most commute to work. Stoke Ferry has some industry associated with agriculture primarily animal feed mill, also a timber yard & agricultural engineers population commutes & works in local industry. Village bypassed in 1985. Scheduled for Development in county struccture plan. Whittington is a small village hamlet which has an animal feed mill on its outskirts.
